text: I accidentally catfished a girl six years older than me, and now she's marrying my brother. Life's weird, right? So here's a wild one for you. When I was 15, I randomly met a girl online. She was 21 and thought I was two. I didn't correct her because why not? I was bored, curious, and honestly, it was kind of fun talking to someone older. Over the next year, we became pretty close friends. We would chat on the phone for hours, sometimes up to 10 hours a day, and no, nothing weird ever happened because well, I'm gay. But this whole thing went on until one day, she dropped a bombshell on me. Out of the blue, she called and casually asked, how are you going to celebrate your 16th birthday? My brain short-circuited, I panicked. I mean, what was I supposed to say? Surprise. I've been lying to you this whole time. So, like any mature 15-year-old, I blocked her everywhere and hoped I could pretend it never happened. Here's the kicker. A few years later, she matched with my brother on Tinder of all people. And when she mentioned me during their chats, everything unraveled. My brother was like, wait, my teenage brother was your 21-year-old online friend? Oof. Fast forward five years. They're now engaged, bought a house, and getting married in May. And me? Not invited. Yep, LMAO.
